# Y2KASE Brand Style Guide

All website pages, sections, snippets, and UI elements must stay visually consistent with the Y2KASE logo. The brand is **Y2K kawaii** — soft pastels, hot pink accents, pixelated retro type, sparkle details, and iridescent/holographic touches.

## Color Palette

| Role | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Primary accent | `#FF4EC7` | Hot magenta — buttons, headings, highlights |
| Background gradient start | `#FFD6EC` | Soft pink |
| Background gradient mid | `#D9B8F5` | Soft lavender/purple |
| Background gradient end | `#B8E4FA` | Baby blue |
| Text on light bg | `#3B1F5E` | Deep purple-navy |
| White/pearl | `#FFFFFF` | Card backgrounds, glows |
| Star/sparkle gold | `#FFE899` | Accent sparkles only |

Never use: plain black (`#000`), stark grey, cool corporate blues, or flat muted tones that clash with the pastel palette.

## Typography

- **Brand/heading font**: pixel or retro 8-bit style (e.g. `Press Start 2P`, `VT323`, or `Silkscreen`) for hero headings and the store name.
- **Body font**: rounded, friendly sans-serif (e.g. `Nunito`, `Poppins`, `Quicksand`).
- Avoid serif fonts, condensed fonts, or anything that feels corporate or neutral.

## Backgrounds & Gradients

Prefer soft diagonal or radial pastel gradients over flat colors:

```css
/* ✅ On-brand background */
background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFD6EC 0%, #D9B8F5 50%, #B8E4FA 100%);

/* ❌ Off-brand */
background: #ffffff;
background: #f5f5f5;
```

## UI Elements

- **Buttons**: hot pink/magenta fill with white text, rounded corners (`border-radius: 999px` pill style), subtle pink glow on hover.
- **Cards/containers**: white or very light pink background, soft box-shadow with a pink or lavender tint, rounded corners (`border-radius: 16px–24px`).
- **Borders**: use light lavender or pink tones; never dark or harsh borders.
- **Icons & motifs**: hearts ♡, stars ✦, butterflies, sparkles — lean into these as decorative accents.
- **Badges/labels**: pastel pill badges (pink, lavender, blue) with dark purple text.

## Iridescent / Holographic Effects

Logo uses rainbow/iridescent elements (glasses, pixel heart). Replicate sparingly with:

```css
/* Holographic shimmer text */
background: linear-gradient(90deg, #FF4EC7, #B8E4FA, #D9B8F5, #FF4EC7);
-webkit-background-clip: text;
-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
background-size: 200%;
animation: shimmer 3s linear infinite;
```

Use only on hero headings or special callouts — not body text.

## Sparkles & Decorative Details

Add `✦` or `✨` sparkle characters or CSS pseudo-elements around key UI touchpoints (hero titles, CTA buttons, section dividers). Keep them subtle — 2–4 per viewport.

## What to Avoid

- Flat, corporate, or minimalist design that strips the playful kawaii energy.
- Dark mode / dark backgrounds (the brand is light and pastel).
- Harsh contrast — everything should feel soft and dreamy.
- Overloading with rainbow — accent sparingly; the base should be pastel.
